body:
We must add a symbol on the operation which has a `Nonlocal` anchor associated with any of its fields.
Parser was not adding symbol when the `circt.nonlocal` is present on a subfield of a Bundle type.

The `LowerTypes` must then fixup the `NonLocalAnchor` after lowering, because the lowered bundle fields 
will get new symbols. This requires the NLA to be updated with the new lowered symbol.

`LowerTypes` should record all the bundle fields which have a reference to the NLA, and the corresponding 
symbol for the subfield. The NLA is then updated at the end of the pass. 


In the following example, the symbol must exist on the `wire` when its field has a `NonLocal` anchor.
And after lowering, the NLA must be updated with the correct symbol.
```
module  {
  firrtl.circuit "Foo"   {
    firrtl.nla @nla_1 [#hw.innerNameRef<@Foo::@bar>, #hw.innerNameRef<@Bar::@b>]
    firrtl.module @Bar() {
      %b = firrtl.wire sym @b  {annotations = [#firrtl.subAnno<fieldID = 2, {circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, three}>]} : !firrtl.bundle<baz: uint<1>, qux: uint<1>>
    }
    firrtl.module @Foo() {
       firrtl.instance bar sym @bar  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Bar()
    }
  }
}
```
